text:
I cropped the primary photo for each product to match the aspect ratio of the edhrecast playmat, and reached out to the Inked guys to see if they could send me or Jason a mockup version of the original playmat that'd match the edhrecast one. Once I get that, I'll make it the primary photo. I also asked them about resolution for the edhrecast drawing, so I'll let you guys know when I hear on that.

I can't find a way in the website editor to change the EDHREC Shop thing-- as far as I can tell this theme just inserts the name of the shop there and you can't change it without messing with the code. Maybe we should just try getting rid of it, or just moving the word "shop" into the navbar to integrate with the logo somehow, but that would require coding, I think. I'm also not sure about adding a border to the photos. I can add it with photoshop to the photo files themselves if we want, but Shopify resizes the photos for various pages, so it might end up making the border change sizes too. We could get <@U28TLDP0R> on that too, but I think we'd have to set a border for every place/page where an image appears.
> Please have resolution of 150 PPI
not sure how that translates to WxH but it probably wasn't that

either way i see having the new edhrecast playmats in with a higher resolution image a blocker for getting the store out, so please figure this out soon <@U33EGB4TX> <@UJHPKDALB>. if he cant put together a higher res version maybe we can put a fancy border around the image and make it smaller
Yeah I’ll pass it on as soon as I hear from them. I figure they’ll probably get back to me today and then we can see what the artist guy can do.
You guys have any thoughts in the meantime on ditching the “EDHREC Shop” heading and/or image borders?
That is on how to implement them <@U28TLDP0R>

just to recap what i want before shop goes live
 - edhrecast playmat grainyness issue is figured out, and re-ordered
 - images are all switched over to the "mockup" style
 - action shots of each item are added to the item page (in addition to the mockup as the main image)
 - borders added around images
 - "EDHREC Shop" centered, removed, i don't know
 - Deckboxes added to the storefront (boxgods, the wood boxes, ultrapro boxes)
 - Deckbox orders placed
 - Don finds a kid to help w/ shipping

All our mats on our site we print at 150 for reference. If you have small text, going at 300 is better.”
